<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-D2C48591-F753-4B8E-97E8-A8C5F4D9A5C7" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-D2C48591-F753-4B8E-97E8-A8C5F4D9A5C7" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Print and wind with a locked tension bar </title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-94560935-D638-4480-81D4-A4514A7B3B52"><p class="- topic/p "><ph class="- topic/ph "><indexterm class="- topic/indexterm ">Winding with locked tension bar</indexterm><indexterm class="- topic/indexterm ">Locked tension bar</indexterm></ph> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Winding media with a locked tension bar is only used for stiff media, in order to prevent media transportation issues. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">User task</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-8A380DA4-9A3D-4942-A1E4-3FDCFD6532DB" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_7EDD718158EF4A1E980DD19CC7D8A2DC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The use of the tension bar is set in the media type configuration in the RIP software. For winding with a locked tension bar, you must select locked tension bar under Winding tension. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure you have placed a take-up roll core on the roll winder. 
</p></li><li id="LI_FA6B064B40BC48B4A1CE90BDAAE240C5" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure you have tape ready. 
</p></li><li id="LI_14DD23BAF724443EA4DB7F8A3CE88E2D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer is ready to print. 
</p></li></ul><note id="GUID-20276C2A-29F1-4386-8EC1-14444A1309EB" class="- topic/note " type="caution"><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Do not position the tension bar when there is no media present. Keep your fingers away because the tension bar can fall down. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The winder has an emergency stopping device; It is located on the winder. Activating this emergency stopping device stops all winder motion. 
</p></li></ul></note></prereq><steps id="GUID-A9B20B6D-3F78-45A2-8F9F-E3195C768CE4" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step id="d35085e67" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the operator panel tap on the <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Output</text></uicontrol></ph> icon. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Output configuration</text></uicontrol>. 
</cmd></step><step id="d35085e80" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Make sure <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Wind the output</text></uicontrol></ph> is set to <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Yes</uicontrol></ph>. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="d35085e92" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure you set the output configuration in time, as you cannot change the configuration once the media has passed the clamp. 
</p></note></info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="d35085e96" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-228855AB-307C-4AB9-9ACF-4F2B9D48FD36-low.png" id="d35085e97" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-228855AB-307C-4AB9-9ACF-4F2B9D48FD36-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Optional (licensed): set <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text "> Wind the printed side</text></uicontrol></ph> to <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text "> Outside</text></uicontrol></ph> or <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Inside</text></uicontrol></ph>. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">The default value is <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text "> Outside</text></uicontrol></ph>. When the setting is not available, the output will be winded with the printed side to the outside. 
</p></info></step><step id="d35085e120" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Start a print job. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer spools the media until it reaches the tape position. The clamp closes and the operator panel gives a message indicating you can tape the media. 
</p></info></step><step id="d35085e126" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Make sure the media guides are out of the way as they can damage the media. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "/><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="d35085e131" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-205B7A15-97F3-4CEE-8427-BC73FA41E6AD-low.png" id="d35085e132" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-205B7A15-97F3-4CEE-8427-BC73FA41E6AD-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="d35085e133" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Take the leading edge of the media and align it on the core. 
</cmd></step><step id="d35085e136" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tape first the center and then the sides of the media to the core, as shown on the operator panel. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">For outside winding feed the media along the front of the core, for inside winding feed the media along the back of the core. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> for outside winding: 
</p><fig id="d35085e144" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-898064C1-D114-4FBB-848C-40381A1A5144-low.png" id="d35085e145" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-898064C1-D114-4FBB-848C-40381A1A5144-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> for inside winding: 
</p><fig id="d35085e148" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-C6DE7792-929D-4527-AD58-2B2BE377A7EA-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C6DE7792-929D-4527-AD58-2B2BE377A7EA-low.png"/></fig><note id="d35085e151" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">In order to prevent winding issues when winding the media in the opposite direction of the roll in the drawer, the media has to be taped with enough tapes over the full width of the roll to straighten the curling edge. 
</p></note></info></step><step id="d35085e154" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Place the tension bar lever in locked position. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="d35085e158" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0C96A077-2A8C-47CE-8AB9-3A51AF962F21-low.png" id="d35085e159" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0C96A077-2A8C-47CE-8AB9-3A51AF962F21-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="d35085e160" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Lift up the tension bar and place it correctly on top of the media. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="d35085e164" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B609AAFE-B291-4047-AA4C-1D155E2F6EF8-low.png" id="d35085e165" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B609AAFE-B291-4047-AA4C-1D155E2F6EF8-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="d35085e166" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the operator panel tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Ready</text></uicontrol></ph>. 
</cmd></step><step id="d35085e174" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Move the media guides towards the middle to align with the media. Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Ready</text></uicontrol>.</ph> 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer starts printing while winding the job. Make sure the tension bar falls into the locked position. 
</p><fig id="d35085e185" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7C43EBFF-C34F-4271-9FD7-61096DA17498-low.png" id="d35085e186" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7C43EBFF-C34F-4271-9FD7-61096DA17498-low.png"/></fig></info></step></steps><postreq id="GUID-0C5BCD5B-64CE-423B-B285-499ACD9AB600" class="- topic/section task/postreq "><p class="- topic/p ">When you want to stop winding you have to cut the media. 
</p></postreq></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-5640945D-DEAD-4222-BF83-C982889BE115.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>User task</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
